         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne, 3/8/74 ¶ Sir ¶  ¶ At a meeting of the Trustees of the Royal Park, held this day, I have laid the letter from the townclerk of Hotham (to yourself and considerately transmitted to me) before...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">74.08.03a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Albert Le Souef</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">A345 Royal Park<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Trustees<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>letter &amp; minute book, p. 58-9, Mitchell Library, State Library of New South Wales, Sydney.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne, 3/8/74</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>At a meeting of the Trustees of the Royal Park, held this day, I have laid the letter from the townclerk of Hotham (to yourself and considerately transmitted to me) before my colleagues, who directed me to inform you that they are adverse to the propositions contained in the application, for the following reasons, because</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">1, they do not feel justified to allow any encroachment on the park-land under their control</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">2, because they are aware of the strong objection of the inhabitants of Brunswick, Flemington and other localities in the vicinity against the depositing of egesta in the neighbourhood of the Park</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">3, because the carts would have to pass the only permanent place for drinking-water in the Park, and thus this water would become deteriorated</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">4, because of the difficulty of enforcing any conditions by which the traffic of nightsoil, if once established, would be<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">discontinued</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>or be so arranged as not to become obnoxious to visitors and neighbours of the Park.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>William Guilfoyle 'had suddenly prohibited the deposit of nightsoil in the Government Domain' (report of Hotham Borough Council deputation to J.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>J. Casey,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Argus</seg>, 17 June 1874, p. 4). A proposal to use the Model Farm adjcent to the Royal Park was supported by the Central Board of Health (<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Age</seg>, 2 July 1874, p. 4),<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>but<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the Council was informed<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>by the Secretary of Lands<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>that nightsoil could not be deposited on any of the Government Reserves (<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">North Melbourne<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">a</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">dvertiser</seg>, 3 July 1874, p. 3). Access to the Model Farm was via Royal Park. For a brief general background to the problems faced in disposing of Melbourne waste, see 'Sewerage',<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <ref target="https://www.emelbourne.net.au/biogs/EM01360b.htm">
                           <seg rend="Hyperlink" style="color: #467886; ">https://www.emelbourne.net.au/biogs/EM01360b.htm</seg>
                        </ref>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(accessed 23 January 2025).<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I have the honor to be Sir</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Your obedient</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd von Mueller</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Hon. Secr. Trustees R. P.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">A. Le Souef Esq</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Hon. Manager Royal Park</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Mr. Randall's letter is herewith returned.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">F. v. M.</p>
         </div>
